00:33:59.716 --> 00:34:00.840
eliminate all these things.

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:01.680
I was just wondering
if you could

00:34:01.680 --> 00:34:02.400
speak to that a little bit.

00:34:02.400 --> 00:34:03.710
MELISSA HARTWIG: Yeah,
there's a million questions

00:34:03.710 --> 00:34:04.709
I would have to ask you.

00:34:04.709 --> 00:34:08.150
So do you have a history of
yo-yo dieting, where you lose,

00:34:08.150 --> 00:34:08.710
then gain.

00:34:08.710 --> 00:34:09.710
AUDIENCE: Kind of, yeah.

00:34:09.710 --> 00:34:10.719
MELISSA HARTWIG:
How long are you

00:34:10.719 --> 00:34:11.900
sleeping every single night?

00:34:11.900 --> 00:34:13.233
What are you doing for exercise?

00:34:13.233 --> 00:34:14.570
Is it high intensity stuff?

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:16.239
Are you adequately
recovering from that?

00:34:16.239 --> 00:34:17.780
What does your life
stress look like?

00:34:17.780 --> 00:34:20.469
We would sit down and have a
serious therapy session for me

00:34:20.469 --> 00:34:23.760
to talk about-- maybe
it's the food, maybe.

00:34:23.760 --> 00:34:27.350
A food journal can be very
helpful in this situation

00:34:27.350 --> 00:34:29.876
because I might say to
you, how are you getting

00:34:29.876 --> 00:34:31.000
after your Whole30, Brooke.

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:31.980
And you're like, I'm
doing pretty well.

00:34:31.980 --> 00:34:34.147
And then if I made you write
down every single thing

00:34:34.147 --> 00:34:36.521
like that, not weighing or
measuring, just write it down,

00:34:36.521 --> 00:34:39.250
you're like, oh, wow, that Luna
Bar and almond milk ice cream's

00:34:39.250 --> 00:34:41.030
coming back a
couple times a week.

00:34:41.030 --> 00:34:43.420
And we were having a
conversation before about

00:34:43.420 --> 00:34:45.406
the bags of the plantain chips.

00:34:45.406 --> 00:34:46.489
You think they're healthy.

00:34:46.489 --> 00:34:49.620
If you hoover one of those,
it is like 560 calories.

00:34:49.620 --> 00:34:51.310
And it's not that
calories don't count.

00:34:51.310 --> 00:34:51.810
Right?

00:34:51.810 --> 00:34:54.920
So it's basically like a
mini-meal all unto itself.

00:34:54.920 --> 00:34:55.940
So maybe a food journal.

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:57.430
Maybe it's the food.

00:34:57.430 --> 00:34:59.845
But maybe food isn't your
biggest issue anymore.

00:34:59.845 --> 00:35:01.970
And maybe it's time to look
at things like caffeine

00:35:01.970 --> 00:35:03.950
consumption and
sleep, or what you're

00:35:03.950 --> 00:35:06.680
doing for training and
recovery, or what's

00:35:06.680 --> 00:35:08.070
going on with your life stress.

00:35:08.070 --> 00:35:11.440
I know a lot of people
who go on vacation

00:35:11.440 --> 00:35:12.982
and immediately,
they lose 10 pounds,

00:35:12.982 --> 00:35:15.190
even though their eating
habits dramatically changed.

00:35:15.190 --> 00:35:16.430
And I'm like, well, shocking.

00:35:16.430 --> 00:35:17.980
You have no stress on vacation.

00:35:17.980 --> 00:35:19.420
Everything's easy and simple.

00:35:19.420 --> 00:35:22.534
So there's just so many
factors that play into that.

00:35:22.534 --> 00:35:24.450
Consider keeping a journal
just for a few days

00:35:24.450 --> 00:35:28.020
after your Whole30, just to see
if stuff is sneaking back in.

00:35:28.020 --> 00:35:30.997
And then maybe consider going to
work with a functional medicine

00:35:30.997 --> 00:35:32.580
doctor, doing some
very basic testing.

00:35:32.580 --> 00:35:35.160
It could be an underlying,
undiagnosed gut infection,

00:35:35.160 --> 00:35:36.110
for example.

00:35:36.110 --> 00:35:38.110
Really common in
some of these cases.

00:35:38.110 --> 00:35:39.950
So it could be a
number of things.

00:35:39.950 --> 00:35:41.757
But it's not always food.

00:35:41.757 --> 00:35:43.590
And I find when people
do multiple Whole30s,

00:35:43.590 --> 00:35:46.170
they want to tie
everything back to food.

00:35:46.170 --> 00:35:47.660
And food is a huge part of it.

00:35:47.660 --> 00:35:49.107
But it's not the only part.

00:35:49.107 --> 00:35:49.940
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:35:49.940 --> 00:35:51.150
MELISSA HARTWIG:
Yeah, you're welcome.

00:35:51.150 --> 00:35:51.690
And good luck.

