The first one is a simple one.

00:36:00.770 --> 00:36:03.660
Just when you travel, how
do you prepare for that?

00:36:03.660 --> 00:36:06.130
And what foods do
you personally have?

00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:09.720
The second one is more like,
I'm curious on your journey

00:36:09.720 --> 00:36:11.180
to actually write this book.

00:36:11.180 --> 00:36:13.810
And I'd be interested
in this because I had

00:36:13.810 --> 00:36:15.820
tons of dietary issues earlier.

00:36:15.820 --> 00:36:18.350
And I was placed on
the low FODMAP diet.

00:36:18.350 --> 00:36:20.990
It's just like
Whole30, but stricter.

00:36:20.990 --> 00:36:22.470
And it was phenomenal.

00:36:22.470 --> 00:36:23.670
It changed my life.

00:36:23.670 --> 00:36:26.120
Now, I'm like very paleo
with a side of sugar.

00:36:26.120 --> 00:36:30.270
And so just curious how
you got to this point.

00:36:30.270 --> 00:36:32.815
Was it you hit some mark,
and then you were like, wow,

00:36:32.815 --> 00:36:33.856
I need to change my life.

00:36:33.856 --> 00:36:35.480
MELISSA HARTWIG: Oh, I did.

00:36:35.480 --> 00:36:38.040
I'll answer the first
question first about travel.

00:36:38.040 --> 00:36:41.310
So my bag on the way for
this book tour was 68 pounds.

00:36:41.310 --> 00:36:43.310
And I'm pretty sure six
pounds of that were meat

00:36:43.310 --> 00:36:45.660
sticks, like jerky sticks.

00:36:45.660 --> 00:36:47.790
So I always pack a
ton of emergency food.

00:36:47.790 --> 00:36:49.249
And I pack a really
healthy protein

00:36:49.249 --> 00:36:51.873
because that's the hardest thing
to find when you're traveling.

00:36:51.873 --> 00:36:53.800
It's easy to find fruit
and nuts and seeds.

00:36:53.800 --> 00:36:56.180
But so I'm packing like
Epic bars and WildBars,

00:36:56.180 --> 00:36:59.307
and DNX bars, and
the meat sticks.

00:36:59.307 --> 00:37:00.890
Literally, if anyone
wants to try one,

00:37:00.890 --> 00:37:03.546
I've got like seven
in my bag right now.

00:37:03.546 --> 00:37:05.420
I do as much research
as I can ahead of time.

00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:08.220
So when I land, I know where
the local health food store.

00:37:08.220 --> 00:37:10.330
I know where the local
grocery store is.

00:37:10.330 --> 00:37:11.810
I know a few good lunch options.

00:37:11.810 --> 00:37:13.870
I've already looked at
the menu to make sure.

00:37:13.870 --> 00:37:16.070
I can wing it anywhere
at this point.

00:37:16.070 --> 00:37:19.320
But I still want to make it
as easy on myself as possible

00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:22.040
so that when I get there,
I already have a plan.

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:24.160
And I'm not stuck
in rush hour traffic

00:37:24.160 --> 00:37:25.920
after a really long
flight super hangry

00:37:25.920 --> 00:37:28.280
with nowhere to go for food.

00:37:28.280 --> 00:37:30.580
I make sure that my
hotel has a refrigerator

00:37:30.580 --> 00:37:33.360
so I can stock up on a few
things at the grocery store.

00:37:33.360 --> 00:37:35.740
So those are some tips
that make it easier.

